# Logs
logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*

node_modules
dist
dist-ssr
*.local

# electron-builder output (throwaway smoke packages + final installers); large
# binary artifacts, rebuildable per-OS, never committed.
release/

# Vitest browser-mode visual-regression transients (actual/diff renders).
.vitest-attachments

# Vitest browser-test screenshot baselines (e.g. chrome.browser.test.tsx's
# __screenshots__/). Per-machine reference renders committed by mistake; they're
# regenerated on first run and must never be versioned.
**/__screenshots__/

# Vitest browser-mode visual-regression BASELINE (reference screenshots).
# CAVEAT: this is a LOCAL-only dev aid, NOT committed. The baseline binary must
# stay out of the source tree / git diff. On a fresh checkout or CI the dir is
# absent, so the browser test regenerates the baseline on first run and detects
# no regression (consistent with PRD 0 having no CI). Visual-regression diffing
# is therefore only meaningful on a machine that already ran the suite once.
.vitest-screenshots

# e2e Windows WebDriver binary (msedgedriver.exe) — downloaded per-machine to
# match the local WebView2 runtime version; never committed.
e2e/.drivers

# Review-evidence screenshots captured from the real WebKitGTK release build
# under WSLg (e.g. .shots/modal-mid-exit.png). A LOCAL-only dev aid proving the
# Motion enter/exit visibly animates — binary, never committed.
/.shots/

# Review-evidence capture specs. These `*.screenshot.cjs` helpers are
# INTENTIONAL local dev tooling: they drive the release app to grab the
# evidence screenshots above. They're deliberately NOT part of the e2e gate
# (the suite globs `**/*.e2e.cjs`, never `*.screenshot.cjs`) and are kept out of
# the tree so a `git add -A` can't accidentally commit them. Run them explicitly
# per the header in each file.
e2e/specs/*.screenshot.cjs

# Depot scratch / prototype mockup HTML (e.g. .depot-tmp/R1-*.html) — transient
# tooling output, never committed.
.depot-tmp/

# Claude Code local working dir (agent worktrees, image cache, settings) and
# scratch diff dumps — local-only tooling artifacts, never committed.
.claude/
.difftmp/

# napi-rs native build artifacts (e.g. crates/nyx-napi/nyx-napi.win32-x64-msvc.node):
# platform-suffixed binaries produced by `napi build`, rebuildable per-platform and
# never committed. The generated loader (index.js) and types (index.d.ts) ARE
# versioned — only the compiled `.node` is ignored.
*.node

# Electron smoke-test stdout/stderr redirection dumps. When a smoke is run by
# hand with shell redirection (e.g. `electron scripts/smoke-single-instance.cjs
# >out.txt 2>err.txt`), these land in apps/electron/. They're throwaway run
# output, never referenced by any script, and must not be committed. Scoped to
# apps/electron so legitimate out.txt/err.txt elsewhere stay tracked.
apps/electron/out.txt
apps/electron/err.txt

# Editor directories and files
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea
.DS_Store
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.sw?

# Cargo workspace build output (root target dir after monorepo restructure)
/target
